'''Camie Loneozner''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] who was a friend of [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] at [[Anchorhead/Legends|Anchorhead]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] between the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] and the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. Her family managed an underground [[Hydroponics/Legends|hydroponic]] garden on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], and bought most of their water from [[Owen Lars/Legends|Owen Lars's]] farm. She hung out at [[Tosche Station/Legends|Tosche Station]] with [[Janek Sunber/Legends|Janek "Tank" Sunber]], [[Laze Loneozner/Legends|Laze "Fixer" Loneozner]], [[Biggs Darklighter/Legends|Biggs Darklighter]], and Skywalker.

==Biography==
===Early Life===
[[File:Camie2-MOSW.png|thumb|left|180px|Camie]]
A young woman who lived in [[Anchorhead/Legends|Anchorhead]] on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], Camie Loneozner's family grew [[Hydroponics/Legends|hydroponics]] gardens underground, buying the water from [[Owen Lars/Legends|Owen Lars]].<ref name="Databank" /> She owned a furred pet.<ref name="Empire 8">[[Empire 8|''Empire'' 8]]</ref>

===Galactic Civil War===
In [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]]<ref name="The New Essential Chronology">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> Camie was at [[Tosche Station/Legends|Tosche Station]] when [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] arrived excitedly, telling the others about a [[Battle of Tatooine (Galactic Civil War)|battle]] above their planet. She, alongside [[Biggs Darklighter/Legends|Biggs Darklighter]] and [[Laze Loneozner/Legends|Fixer]], followed Luke outside to see the battle with Luke's [[Macrobinoculars/Legends|macrobinoculars]]. The battle appeared to have ended and Camie ridiculed him for making it all up.<ref name="Star Wars: A New Hope novelization">[[Star Wars: A New Hope (novelization)|''Star Wars: A New Hope'' novelization]]</ref>

After the deaths of [[Owen Lars/Legends|Owen]] and [[Beru Whitesun Lars/Legends|Beru Lars]], some of the locals believed that their nephew had murdered them. Camie Loneozner, having spent much time with him, didn't believe those rumors at all. After the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], she told this to historian [[Voren Na'al/Legends|Voren Na'al]] in an interview.<ref name="GG1">''[[Galaxy Guide 1: A New Hope]]''</ref>

Camie was involved with Laze Loneozner, whom she eventually married at some point between [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and [[Biggs Darklighter/Legends|Biggs Darklighter]]'s departures from [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]]<ref name="InsideSWT" /> and the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]].<ref name="Databank" /> Laze Loneozner built an illegal [[Podracer/Legends|podracer]] to sell in order to raise enough funds for a lavish wedding party for her.<ref name="InsideSWT">''[[Inside the Worlds of Star Wars Trilogy]]''</ref>

When [[Tagge Company/Legends|TaggeCo]] decided to test their [[Omega Frost/Legends|Omega Frost]] technology on Tatooine, they bought up a number of the local [[Moisture farm/Legends|moisture farms]]. The Loneozners took over the operations of the old [[Darklighter family/Legends|Darklighter]] farm and were hired by the Tagges to take care of all of the local properties.<ref name="MC31">[[Star Wars (1977) 31|''Star Wars'' (1977) 31]]</ref>

The two Loneozners ran into Luke Skywalker when he returned to Tatooine on a mission for the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebellion]]. They feared that Skywalker might cause trouble and ruin their relationship with the [[House of Tagge/Legends|Tagges]], and so they reported him to the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperials]]. However, Fixer Loneozner had second thoughts about turning in his old friend and decided to warn Skywalker about the Imperials, allowing the young Rebel to escape capture.<ref name="MC31" />

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:CamieLoneozner.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Camie]]
Camie was portrayed by [[Koo Stark]] in ''A New Hope'', though her scenes were not used in the final film release. Her deleted scenes appeared in the first issue of the [[Star Wars (1977)|''Marvel Star Wars'']] comics adaptation of ''A New Hope'',<ref name="Star Wars 1977 1">[[Star Wars (1977) 1|''Star Wars'' (1977) 1]]</ref> and she also appeared in [[Star Wars (1977) 17|''Star Wars'' (1977) 17]] and [[Star Wars (1977) 31|''Star Wars'' (1977) 31]].<ref name="Star Wars 1977 17">[[Star Wars (1977) 17|''Star Wars'' (1977) 17]]</ref><ref name="MC31" /> The lost scenes from ''A New Hope'' can be seen in ''[[Star Wars: Behind the Magic]]''.<ref name="Star Wars: Behind the Magic">''[[Star Wars: Behind the Magic]]''</ref>

She was portrayed by [[Stephanie Steele]] for the [[Star Wars (radio)|''Star Wars Radio Drama'']] on National Public Radio.<ref name="A Wind" />

Her name has sometimes been misspelled as "Cammie".<ref name="Star Wars Journal: The Fight for Justice">''[[Star Wars Journal: The Fight for Justice]]''</ref><ref name="Star Wars Galaxies: An Empire Divided">{{GalaxiesAED}}</ref>

An action figure released by Hasbro in 2010 ''[[Star Wars: Shadows of the Dark Side]]'' set gave Camie the last name "Marstrap", a name that was once given to another of Luke Skywalker's friends, [[Windy Starkiller|Windy]]. Windy was later given the last name "Starkiller", which was considered canonical in the continuity of [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]].<ref name="Hasbro">{{HasbroCite|set=Star Wars: Shadows of the Dark Side|pack=(Celebration V Exclusive) Camie Marstrap & Laze "Fixer" Loneozner|altlink=https://www.rebelscum.com/tvcEXC5_Camie-Fixer.asp}}</ref>

